**Privacy Policy for Yamu Taxi**

_Last updated: November 05, 2024_

**1. Introduction**
This Privacy Policy describes how Yamu Taxi ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and shares personal information when you use our mobile application ("Services"). By using our app, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.

**2. What Information Do We Collect?**
- **Personal Information Provided by You**: When you register or use our Services, we may collect information such as your name, phone number, email address, and payment details.
- **Application Data**:
  - **Location Information**: With your permission, we collect location data to enable real-time taxi tracking and estimated time of arrival.
  - **Push Notifications**: We may send push notifications for important updates related to your account, trip status, or promotions. You may opt out by adjusting your device settings.

**3. How Do We Process Your Information?**
We process your information for the following purposes:
- **Account Management**: To help you set up and manage your account securely.
- **Service Delivery**: To facilitate booking and tracking of rides.
- **Communication**: To provide customer support and respond to inquiries.
- **Improvement**: To analyze usage and improve our Services and offerings.

**4. When and With Whom Do We Share Your Information?**
- **Service Providers**: We may share your information with third-party service providers to help operate and improve our Services.
- **Business Transfers**: In the event of a merger or acquisition, your information may be transferred to the new entity.
- **Compliance**: We may share information to comply with legal obligations.

**5. Do We Use Cookies and Other Tracking Technologies?**
Yes, we use cookies and similar tracking technologies to improve your experience, for analytics, and to tailor ads to your interests.

**6. How Long Do We Keep Your Information?**
We retain your personal information only as long as necessary to provide the Services, comply with legal obligations, and resolve disputes. When we no longer need your information, we will securely delete or anonymize it.

**7. How Do We Keep Your Information Safe?**
We implement technical and organizational measures to protect your information. However, no online transmission or storage method is 100% secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.

**8. What Are Your Privacy Rights?**
Depending on your location, you may have certain rights regarding your personal information. You can contact us to review, update, or delete your data, subject to applicable laws.

**9. Do Not Track Features**
Most web browsers offer Do-Not-Track (DNT) settings. We do not currently respond to DNT signals, as there is no industry standard for handling these requests.

**10. Changes to This Privacy Policy**
We may update our Privacy Policy as necessary. We will notify you of any changes by posting the updated policy here. Please review this Privacy Policy periodically.

**11. Contact Us**
If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at [contact details].

